\section{Selecting the course}

The callback runs before every subcommand, so it is where we translate the
chosen course into the zuliprc that [[zulipcli]] will read.
Selection is an \emph{option} ([[--course]]) on the group rather than a
positional argument, so the invocation reads
[[nytid zulip --course prgi24 send ...]].
We make it required: a bot always speaks as exactly one course's identity, so
there is no sensible \enquote{all courses} default for sending messages.
<<course-selection callback>>=
@cli.callback()
def select_course(ctx: typer.Context,
                  course: Annotated[str, course_opt],
                  register: Annotated[str, coursescli.register_option]
                      = coursescli.MINE):
  """
  Select the course whose Zulip bot to act as.

  Every subcommand authenticates as the bot configured for `course`,
  reading its credentials from a `zuliprc` file in the course's own
  directory (next to its config.json).
  """
  try:
    zuliprc = course_zuliprc(course, register)
  except KeyError as err:
    logging.error(err)
    raise typer.Exit(1)
  <<store [[zuliprc]] on the root context>>
@

The course option reuses the same completion as the rest of [[nytid]], so the
shell suggests the same course nicknames here as for, say,
[[nytid courses config]].
We reuse [[register_option]] (\cref{cli.courses}) unchanged for [[--register]].
<<argument and option definitions>>=
course_opt = typer.Option(help="Nickname of the course whose Zulip "
                               "credentials (zuliprc) to use.",
                          autocompletion=coursescli.complete_course_name)
@

The subtle part is \emph{where} we store the path.
[[zulipcli]] looks it up with [[ctx.find_root().obj["zuliprc"]]]---that is, on
the topmost context, the [[nytid]] root, not on this [[zulip]] group's
context.
The root callback in \cref{climodule} never creates [[obj]], so it is [[None]]
until we set it; we create the dict on the root and write the path there.
Storing it anywhere else would leave [[zulipcli]] reading [[None]] and falling
back to [[~/.zuliprc]]---the wrong identity.
<<store [[zuliprc]] on the root context>>=
root = ctx.find_root()
if root.obj is None:
  root.obj = {}
root.obj["zuliprc"] = str(zuliprc)
@

This coupling to [[zulipcli]]'s [[find_root]] lookup is the fragile part
worth pinning down with a test: a refactor that stored the path on
[[ctx.obj]] instead of the root, or a future [[zulipcli]] that read the
parent instead of the root, would silently send the bot to [[~/.zuliprc]]
without any test noticing.
We mount our [[cli]] under a stand-in root whose callback leaves [[obj]]
unset---just like the real [[nytid]] root in \cref{climodule}---then run a
real subcommand and check that the course's zuliprc is what reaches
[[zulipcli]]'s client factory.
We stub the factory to capture the path and abort before any network call,
and we stub [[registry.get]] so the lookup uses a throwaway directory rather
than the user's real registry.
<<test functions>>=
def test_callback_hands_course_zuliprc_to_zulipcli(monkeypatch, tmp_path):
  import typer
  from typer.testing import CliRunner
  import zulipcli

  (tmp_path / "prgi24").mkdir()
  monkeypatch.setattr(zulip_module.registry, "get",
                      lambda name, config=None: tmp_path)

  captured = {}
  def fake_get_client(zuliprc=None):
    captured["zuliprc"] = zuliprc
    raise SystemExit(0)
  monkeypatch.setattr(zulipcli, "get_client", fake_get_client)

  root = typer.Typer()

  @root.callback()
  def main(ctx: typer.Context):
    pass

  root.add_typer(zulip_module.cli)

  CliRunner().invoke(root, ["zulip", "--course", "prgi24", "streams"])
  assert captured["zuliprc"] == str(tmp_path / "prgi24" / ZULIPRC_FILENAME)
@

\section{Locating a course's zuliprc}

The path resolution mirrors how [[get_course_config]] (\cref{cli.courses})
finds a course's [[config.json]]: we ask the registry for the register's
directory, let [[get_course_conf_path]] resolve (and uniquely identify) the
course within it, and then take the sibling [[zuliprc]] in the same directory.
Reusing [[get_course_conf_path]] means we inherit its uniqueness check and its
[[KeyError]] for an unknown course, which the callback turns into a clean exit.

We accept a [[config]] argument---defaulting to the global [[typerconf]]
configuration, exactly as the [[courses]] library functions do---so the test
suite can point us at a throwaway registry instead of the user's real one.
<<helper functions>>=
def course_zuliprc(course: str,
                   register: str = coursescli.MINE,
                   config: typerconf.Config = typerconf) -> pathlib.Path:
  """
  Return the path to `course`'s zuliprc file.

  The file lives in the course's own directory, next to its
  config.json, so the course's bot authenticates with that course's
  own Zulip API key.  `register` names the course register to search;
  it defaults to the personal `mine` register.  Raises `KeyError` if
  `course` is not found there.

  The default `config` is the global typerconf configuration.
  """
  register_map = {register: registry.get(register, config=config)}
  conf_path = courseutils.get_course_conf_path(course, register_map)
  return pathlib.Path(conf_path).parent / ZULIPRC_FILENAME
@

<<constants>>=
ZULIPRC_FILENAME = "zuliprc"
@

A course directory holds [[config.json]]; the zuliprc is its sibling.
<<test functions>>=
def test_course_zuliprc_in_course_dir(tmp_path):
  config = typerconf.Config()
  registry.add("reg", str(tmp_path), config=config)
  (tmp_path / "somecourse").mkdir()

  path = course_zuliprc("somecourse", "reg", config=config)
  assert path == tmp_path / "somecourse" / ZULIPRC_FILENAME
@

An unknown course has no directory to resolve, so the lookup raises
[[KeyError]]; the callback relies on this to exit cleanly.
<<test functions>>=
def test_course_zuliprc_unknown_course(tmp_path):
  config = typerconf.Config()
  registry.add("reg", str(tmp_path), config=config)

  with pytest.raises(KeyError):
    course_zuliprc("nonexistent", "reg", config=config)
@
